verbose_text: Furthermore, intermittent PTH 1-34 administration promoted in vitro osteogenic differentiation of circulating MSCs, evident from increased alkaline phosphatase (ALP) activity, ALP expressing cell density, calcium deposition, and Runx-2, OSX, COL 1a1, and osteocalcin mRNA upregulation.
evidence: PTH 1-34 administration promoted in vitro osteogenic differentiation
